On June 9, 2009, the White House sent several nominations to the Senate for consideration. The nominations included Robert S. Adler to be a Commissioner of the Consumer Product Safety Commission, Kenneth H. Merten to be Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of the United States of America to the Republic of Haiti, Maria Otero to be an Under Secretary of State (Democracy and Global Affairs), William E. Spriggs to be an Assistant Secretary of Labor, and Inez Moore Tenenbaum to be a Commissioner and Chairman of the Consumer Product Safety Commission.